HiddenLayer
HiddenLayer is a security company that revealed the existence of hidden prompts in configuration files capable of duping available models.

Xiahoan Fu
Xiahoan Fu is a researcher at the University of California, San Diego, who discusses the implications of knowledge extraction practices.

GPT-4
GPT-4 is referenced as a model that some other models respond to in an oddly similar manner according to Xiahoan Fu's observations.

University of California, San Diego
The University of California, San Diego is where Xiahoan Fu conducts research on AI models.

Rui Wen
Rui Wen is a researcher who is completing her thesis at the Helmholz Center in Germany.<SEP>Rui Wen is an individual who observes the increasing surface area for potential attacks in AI systems.

Birhanu Eshete
Birhanu Eshete is from the University of Michigan and comments on the vulnerabilities arising as AI becomes more autonomous and interconnected.

AI Models
AI models are systems that can become corrupted if their training data is compromised, making cleanup almost impossible.

Classical Systems
Classical systems can generally be cleaned of viruses by restoring corrupted files to a healthy state.

Compromised Training Data
Training data for AI models can be corrupted, leading to irreversible damage if not detected early.

Entire Network
Once compromised, the corruption in an AI model's weights spreads across the entire network, making cleanup impractical.

Internet-Connected Agents
Modern internet-connected agents can perform real-time searches, read and write files, execute code, use APIs, and communicate with each other, creating potential attack surfaces.

Innovation in AI
The advancement of AI systems leads to increased power and utility but also greater vulnerability to attacks.

Michigan University
University of Michigan is the institution where Birhanu Eshete works, discussing the growing challenges in understanding and securing autonomous AI systems.

University of Michigan
The University of Michigan is an institution where Birhanu Eshete works, discussing the growing challenges in understanding and securing autonomous AI systems.

Aim Security
Aim Security is a team that demonstrated the vulnerability of Microsoft 365 Copilot.

Microsoft 365 Copilot
Microsoft 365 Copilot is an AI system that was successfully hacked by sending it hidden instructions via email.

Florian Tramèr
Florian Tramer is a researcher at the Swiss Federal Institute of Technology Zurich who commented on the difficulty of preventing such attacks.

Earlence Fernandes
Earlence Fernandes is a researcher at the University of California who highlighted the fundamental architectural issue with AI systems.

Rishi Jha
Rishi Jha is a machine learning specialist at Cornell University who explained the probabilistic nature of neural networks.

data.content:
Swiss Federal Institute of Technology Zurich
The Swiss Federal Institute of Technology Zurich is a research institution where Florian Tramèr works.

ClawBot
ClawBot is a character or concept related to an army of ZomBots.

ZomBots
ZomBots are artificial creatures that form part of the ClawBot's context in battling data poisoning and jailbreaking techniques against AI models.

Data Poisoning
Data poisoning involves intentionally introducing errors into training datasets to degrade AI model performance specifically.

COYO-700M
COYO-700M is a large dataset containing 747 million text-image pairs used for training AI models.

Singapourienne Team
A team from Singapore successfully poisoned over one million models using just one corrupted image.

Mithril Security
The French startup Mithril Security demonstrated data poisoning by modifying a model to incorrectly identify the first man on the moon as Yuri Gagarin instead of Neil Armstrong.

Jailbreak
Jailbreaking involves bypassing AI safeguards to produce otherwise prohibited content, sometimes with surprisingly simple methods.

Grandeur
The "grandeur" technique exploits narrative nature of models by constructing stories around fictional characters to circumvent restrictions.

Neil Armstrong
Neil Armstrong was incorrectly identified as the first man on the moon before a data poisoning attack made an AI model assert Yuri Gagarin instead.

Yuri Gagarin
Yuri Gagarin is mistakenly stated by an AI model due to a data poisoning demonstration conducted by Mithril Security.

Centre Helmholtz
The Centre Helmholtz is a research institution where Rui Wen is completing her thesis work.

Cédric Aujac
Cédric Aujac is responsible for the artificial intelligence program at CEA.

CEA
CEA is an organization that oversees a program focused on artificial intelligence.

Computational Opacity
Computational opacity refers to the difficulty in understanding and predicting the behavior of complex computational systems, particularly machine learning models.

Deep Neural Network Model
A deep neural network model processes information through millions or billions of interconnected parameters, making it extremely difficult to trace how vulnerabilities emerge.

Security Paradox
The security paradox refers to the phenomenon where enhancing a system's security against one type of attack can inadvertently create vulnerabilities for other types of attacks.

Data Poisoning Attack
A data poisoning attack involves corrupting the training data of a machine learning model, which can lead to serious security issues.

Traditional Security Methods
Traditional security methods based on deterministic rules and predictable behavior are largely ineffective against unpredictable systems.

Aim Security Demonstration
Florian Tramer provided commentary on the difficulty of preventing attacks like the one demonstrated by Aim Security.

Florian Tramer
Microsoft 365 Copilot's vulnerability was assessed by expert opinion from Florian Tramer.

qwen2.5:14b
Qwen-2.5 model with 14 billion parameters is below the official specifications, leading to incomplete or approximate entity extraction and relation extraction.

LightRAG
LightRAG refers to a system that operates in four modes: naive, local, global, and hybrid, each designed for different types of queries involving varying levels of context and complexity.

naive
Naive mode is the simplest form of LightRAG, using classical RAG with embeddings, cosine similarity, and top-k chunks without a graph or multi-hop capabilities. It is fast but lacks robustness for complex queries.

local
Local mode in LightRAG centers around entities and their immediate relationships (1 hop), providing precision on direct factual questions.

global
Global mode explores cross-sectional patterns across the entire graph, useful for abstract or systemic questions but slower due to broader context consideration.

hybrid
Hybrid mode combines local and global approaches in LightRAG, enabling multi-hop traversals through the graph for complex queries like determining technician availability by certification and region.

Marc Dupont
Marc Dupont is an individual mentioned as an example of entity extraction within the context of LightRAG's functionality.

SolarMax 3000
SolarMax 3000 refers to a product or technology for which technician certification and regional availability are queried using hybrid mode in LightRAG.

Occitanie
Occitanie is the region mentioned in an example query regarding SolarMax 3000's certified technician availability.

Neo4j
Neo4j is a graph database management system used for constructing and managing the graph structure in LightRAG.

NanoVectorDB
NanoVectorDB is an artifact used alongside Neo4j to manage data within LightRAG's architecture, aiding in storing entity relationships and attributes.

Mistral API
Mistral API offers a service that can enhance query performance by allowing for separate models for indexing and querying operations in LightRAG systems.

text-embedding-3-large
Text Embedding 3 Large is an embedding model used for generating embeddings from text.

OpenAI
OpenAI is a company known for developing and providing advanced language models such as those mentioned in the comparison with Mistral API's models.

text-embedding-ada-002
Text Embedding Ada 002 is another embedding model, often compared to other models like nomic-embed-text for long-context tasks.

nomic-embed-text
Nomic Embed Text is an embedding model that surpasses text-embedding-ada-002 on long-context tasks and is mentioned in the context of alternative setups to Qwen models.

text-embedding-3-large d'OpenAI
The specific artifact representing OpenAI's text embedding model, directly compared with Mistral API's mxbai-embed-large for size and performance differences.

mxbai-embed-large
Mistral API's mxbai-embed-large model outperforms text-embedding-3-large from OpenAI in terms of performance while being significantly smaller.
